  publisher = {Association for Computing Machinery},
  abstract  = {We describe OMRAT, an online tool for semi-automatic annotation of music scores for Optical Music Recognition (OMR) systems. OMRAT uses deep neural networks, machine learning, and music notation ontologies at different stages to respectively detect musical objects, establish relationships between them, and convert them into a machine-readable format MEI. A human editor verifies the output of the recognition stage to correct potential errors and remove incorrect labels as needed.},
